Fast JSON Parser for .NET

39% less time than Newtonsoft.Json using 31% less memory. (Comparison measured on an M2 MacBook Pro Max.)

Uses ReadOnlyMemory<char> instead of string for speed and memory efficiency.

Kept simple. No dependencies. No support for JSONPath or LINQ to JSON. No support for deserialization to .NET objects
or serialization from them. No support for JSON5 or JSON Schema. Only single file needed (J.cs).

Does not parse JSON literals to value types, such as booleans, null or numbers. Since JSON numbers are not bounded by
rules of IEEE 754 floating point, they can be arbitrarily large or precise.